Dialogue: 2,0:06:50.77,0:06:56.65,1080EN,,0,0,0,,buildup? As the blood flows around in your body you could say maybe myoglobin could accumulate in your heart but
Dialogue: 1,0:06:56.65,0:07:02.53,1080CN,,0,0,0,,但心脏没东西能留住肌红蛋白。蛋白质是大分子，可能只是穿过心脏几个腔就走了
Dialogue: 2,0:06:56.65,0:07:02.53,1080EN,,0,0,0,,there's nothing there to catch it. Protein is a large molecule and would likely just pass through the chambers of the heart
Dialogue: 1,0:07:02.53,0:07:08.71,1080CN,,0,0,0,,没有留的地方自然积累不起来。那肝脏呢？肝脏就是参与蛋白质代谢的
Dialogue: 2,0:07:02.53,0:07:08.71,1080EN,,0,0,0,,There isn't a reservoir where it can accumulate. But how about the liver? Well the liver breaks proteins down so
Dialogue: 1,0:07:08.71,0:07:15.70,1080CN,,0,0,0,,更不可能积累在肝脏。但肾脏呢？肾单位，是肾脏的功能单元
Dialogue: 2,0:07:08.71,0:07:15.70,1080EN,,0,0,0,,it's probably not going to buildup there either. But what about the kidney? The nephron, the functional unit of the
Dialogue: 1,0:07:15.70,0:07:22.03,1080CN,,0,0,0,,包含很多细小管腔。它们筛出血液中的毒物
